The UV–visible spectrum study is an important tool to confirm the formation of nanoparticles. Fig. S1 shows the UV–vis spectrum of N-Undoped CDs which exhibit the absorption peak at 277 nm and 332 nm which are the corresponding peak positions for n-π* and π-π*, moreover we have measured the emission spectrum of the Undoped CDs and the emission maximum was observed at 440 nm. Color of the solution in day light is yellow; meanwhile it’s become a cyan color under UV-light irradiations. Whereas, the N-doped CDs shows the absorption peak at 278 nm 332 nm which are the corresponding position for n-π* and π-π* carbon dot transitions [21]. The emission spectrum maximum of the N-Doped was found at 473 nm, color of the solution is yellow under day light were as become green in under UV-light (Fig. 1
                        ; Inset) (see Fig. 2
                        ).

XRD pattern of the N-Doped CDs is shown in Fig. 3
                        . The XRD pattern of N- CDs exhibits the (002) and (100) planes at 30.140 and 40.500 respectively. The XRD data is confirmed that the obtained CDs are amorphous nature [26]. The 30.140 confirm the amorphous nature of the CDs was formed and tightly packed alkyl chains present in the CDs [27] (see Fig. 4
                        ).

X-ray photoelectron spectroscopy is a very important tool for finding out the nature of chemical species present in the synthesized N-CDs. The Fig. 7
                        .A shows the survey spectrum of XPS of N-CDs. Here we have been observed C1s, N1s, and O1s at 285 eV, 404 eV and 531 eV, respectively. The chemical species of C1s (Fig. 7 B) we have observed at 286.5 eV, 288.5 eV, 290.9 eV in the deconvoluted spectrum COC, OCO, CO at respective positions. These results confirms that the synthesis N-CDs having the functionality of COC, OCO, CO functionalities. Were as in the case of N1s (Fig. 7 C) here we have observed the spectrum at 404 eV. The deconvoluted spectrum we have observed three peaks which have corresponding to the CN, CN, ONC at 400.04 eV, 401.48 eV, 402.89 eV, respectively. Finally adjacent one chemical species peak of O1s (Fig. 7 D) obtained at 533.10 eV, 534.41 eV in the deconvoluted CO, OCO chemical species we have been observed. These results are clearly confirm that the synthesis N-CDs having the functionality of epoxy and carboxyl groups, hydroxyl groups, CC, CC functionalities [29] (see Figs. 8–10


                        ).
